I'm Loony Lilly Bainbridge?

22:02.487 --> 22:05.240
You're not loony.
Not to me.

22:11.330 --> 22:14.291
What happened that day? With your dad.

22:20.088 --> 22:22.507
Sorry, I shouldn't have--

22:27.220 --> 22:29.264
My mom and I went to pick up my dad.

22:31.350 --> 22:34.436
He worked at the jarring plant
out on Willoughby.

22:34.978 --> 22:37.105
You know, pickles and stuff.

22:37.773 --> 22:40.609
We were leaving the factory
when I realized

22:40.692 --> 22:42.611
I'd forgotten something inside.

22:43.779 --> 22:47.657
This mood ring
I just bought at the five-and-dime.

22:48.950 --> 22:51.661
It was just a cheap, stupid toy,

22:51.745 --> 22:53.497
but he went back to get it.

22:54.873 --> 22:58.502
And I don't know-- I don't know,
one of the machines jammed up.

23:00.462 --> 23:04.007
It wasn't even his station, but my dad,

23:05.550 --> 23:07.135
he always wanted to help.

23:10.472 --> 23:12.349
They said he climbed into the gears.

23:14.017 --> 23:16.436
I guess he thought
he'd killed the power, but--

23:17.437 --> 23:19.898
When the foreman realized
it was on another station,

23:19.981 --> 23:21.358
it was too late.

23:23.902 --> 23:25.529
If I hadn't made him go back--

23:25.612 --> 23:26.947
You couldn't have known.

23:28.407 --> 23:30.075
It was just a terrible accident.

23:52.764 --> 23:54.015
Happy New Year.

23:56.101 --> 23:57.978
Thanks for letting me talk about it.

23:58.603 --> 23:59.855
No one else does.

24:00.605 --> 24:03.567
Not Marge. Or the Pattycakes.

24:04.067 --> 24:05.485
You're not like those girls.

24:06.528 --> 24:07.946
Starting to realize that.

24:09.030 --> 24:10.782
For better or for worse, I guess.

24:11.408 --> 24:12.659
For better.

24:26.131 --> 24:28.508
I'm sorry. That was stupid.

24:28.592 --> 24:30.218
No, it's okay.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.095
It's just that we're friends.

24:32.179 --> 24:33.805
It's fine, really.

24:33.889 --> 24:36.308
It is. I should head back anyway.

24:37.100 --> 24:39.769
If my pop catches me out of bed
at this hour, he'll--

24:42.355 --> 24:43.899
I didn't mean it like that.

24:46.359 --> 24:47.777
I gotta go.

24:48.904 --> 24:50.447
Matty, wait!

25:03.335 --> 25:04.336
Lilly.

25:06.254 --> 25:08.673
Don't forget to lay your clothes out
for tomorrow morning.

25:11.927 --> 25:12.928
Remember?

25:13.678 --> 25:16.097
We're going to visit
your father at the cemetery.

25:17.974 --> 25:21.353
If it's all the same,
I don't think I'm gonna go.

25:24.564 --> 25:25.565
It's been a year.

25:26.358 --> 25:28.735
You haven't visited his grave even once.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.446
I know. I'm just...

25:32.948 --> 25:34.074
not ready.

25:39.329 --> 25:42.457
You're not the only person
to have something awful happen to them.

25:43.708 --> 25:45.710
The sooner you realize that, the better.

25:47.087 --> 25:48.755
Don't forget to take your medication.

26:03.687 --> 26:06.106
Friends, the idle brain
is the devil's playground.

26:06.189 --> 26:08.900
Shameless music that'll grab your son

26:08.984 --> 26:12.070
and your daughter with the arms
of a jungle animal instinct.

26:12.153 --> 26:13.280
Mass'steria!

26:14.614 --> 26:17.617
We got trouble.
Right here in River City.

26:18.994 --> 26:20.954
Trouble! Trouble! Trouble! Trouble!

26:21.037 --> 26:23.415
Trouble! Trouble!
Trouble! Trouble! Trouble!

26:23.498 --> 26:24.624
Matty, is that you?

26:26.501 --> 26:27.669
Where are you?

26:31.089 --> 26:33.550
Matty, if it's you, if you can hear me,

26:33.633 --> 26:36.678
just come home, all right?
Just please come home.

26:39.973 --> 26:41.391
He won't let me!

26:52.736 --> 26:56.990
Matty Clements speaking to you
through the pipes?

26:57.240 --> 26:58.366
Just forget it.

26:59.534 --> 27:02.037
And seeing as how you barely
said one word to this kid

27:02.120 --> 27:04.331
when he was alive,
why is it that he's reaching out to you

27:04.414 --> 27:05.582
from beyond the grave?

27:11.171 --> 27:12.922
-Hi, Patty.
-Hi, Margie.

27:13.590 --> 27:14.883
Just a sec.

27:16.051 --> 27:18.178
-Come here.
-What are you doing?

27:19.179 --> 27:20.472
What are you doing?

27:20.972 --> 27:23.600
Making sure none of her friends
hear you talking like this

27:23.683 --> 27:25.560
because what you're saying is crazy.

27:25.644 --> 27:26.895
And I don't mean to use that word.

27:26.978 --> 27:28.688
-I don't--
-I know what I heard.

27:30.273 --> 27:31.524
Listen to me.

27:32.025 --> 27:33.610
We've only got
two more months till summer.

27:33.693 --> 27:35.528
Let's just get through them
without giving everyone

27:35.612 --> 27:37.322
something new to whisper about you.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.242
About me or about us?

27:44.162 --> 27:45.622
What's that supposed to mean?

27:49.042 --> 27:50.168
It wasn't me.

27:56.675 --> 27:58.718
Are you worried about
what people will think of me

27:58.802 --> 28:01.846
or what Patty and all of them
will think of you because of me?

28:03.223 --> 28:06.643
Jesus, Lill, I'm trying to be your friend,

28:06.726 --> 28:09.104
but sometimes you make it really hard.

28:15.193 --> 28:16.444
That's my point, Teds.

28:16.653 --> 28:18.905
There has to be a reason
why men have nipples.

28:18.988 --> 28:20.031
Think about it.

28:20.365 --> 28:22.909
Maybe it's like
when we used to have tails and gills

28:22.992 --> 28:24.369
and we just evolved out of it.

28:24.452 --> 28:26.329
Or it's nature's way of telling us

28:26.413 --> 28:28.123
that we're second in line
to feed our babies

28:28.206 --> 28:29.499
should anything happen to women.

28:29.582 --> 28:31.334
Like aliens taking them back
to their world.

28:31.418 --> 28:32.419
When that day comes,

28:32.502 --> 28:34.921
you and I are gonna be
breastfeeding like crazy.

28:40.218 --> 28:41.511
What are you doing here?

28:42.887 --> 28:45.807
And how much of that did you hear?

28:47.434 --> 28:49.102
I need to talk to you guys.

28:49.352 --> 28:50.603
Talk to us? About what?

28:50.687 --> 28:53.648
About how they found her dad's body parts
in pickle jars all over Maine?

28:53.732 --> 28:55.692
That's bullshit. It never happened.

28:58.403 --> 28:59.988
He swore he'd keep his mouth shut.

29:00.488 --> 29:02.490
We only brought him here, like, one time.

29:03.074 --> 29:05.660
One time? Weren't you guys best friends?

29:05.785 --> 29:07.120
It's complicated.

29:07.245 --> 29:09.205
Okay, so you're positive
it was Matty, right?

29:09.414 --> 29:11.040
It was his voice, I'm sure.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.501
I don't know what it means. I just--

29:13.585 --> 29:14.753
I thought if anyone would care,

29:14.961 --> 29:17.422
if anyone would believe me,
it'd be you guys.

29:19.132 --> 29:21.509
Don't tell me you're buying
into this cock-a-doodle story.

29:21.718 --> 29:23.011
You mean cockamamie?

29:23.094 --> 29:25.096
It's both of those things. Okay?
This story's insane.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.264
Look who it's coming from.

29:27.432 --> 29:32.771
I know. It sounds impossible,
but maybe it's just improbable.

29:33.438 --> 29:36.775
Teddy, for this to be true,
Matty would have to still be alive.

29:36.858 --> 29:38.526
And he'd have to know
where every single one

29:38.610 --> 29:40.445
of Derry's pipes start and end.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.865
And the exact time that Lilly
was about to take a bath.

29:44.532 --> 29:46.576
And how to aim his voice
down a certain pipe

29:46.659 --> 29:49.370
so he could stick his little finger
up there and wave hello to her.

29:49.996 --> 29:54.334
Phil, you've explained one hundred ways
how aliens have come to Earth.

29:55.084 --> 29:58.004
Tracking our smells,
pretending to be dogs,

29:58.838 --> 30:00.673
-probing our anus.
-"Ani."

30:01.466 --> 30:04.427
You've "proven" all of that to me,

30:04.511 --> 30:06.304
yet you can't just believe

30:06.387 --> 30:11.309
that Matty is trying to get in contact
with someone he actually knows?

30:11.768 --> 30:13.436
So, you do believe me?

30:15.855 --> 30:16.981
Look...

30:18.191 --> 30:20.235
Lilly, I want to. I'm trying to.

30:21.986 --> 30:23.655
There's plenty
of unbelievable things out there

30:23.738 --> 30:26.157
that people believe,
and I'm sure some of them are true.

30:27.992 --> 30:30.203
I'm just not so sure about this one.

30:40.380 --> 30:42.215
I can't believe you gave her your soda.

30:57.981 --> 30:58.982
Come on in, Major.

31:02.151 --> 31:03.361
I wanted you to know that Masters

31:03.444 --> 31:05.488
is gonna spend the week
on latrine duty.

31:06.155 --> 31:08.908
And a citation is going
on his permanent flight record.

31:10.243 --> 31:12.912
I won't stand for that kind
of horseshit on my base.

31:15.081 --> 31:16.374
To less horseshit.

31:23.756 --> 31:26.426
I understand you served
under General Abbott in Korea.

31:27.552 --> 31:28.720
As he tells it, you, Major,

31:28.803 --> 31:31.180
are about the bravest, damn pilot
he's ever met.

31:31.848 --> 31:34.267
You flew a B-29 up MiG Alley
into the teeth

31:34.350 --> 31:36.603
of Soviet anti-aircraft fire at Sui-ho,

31:37.437 --> 31:39.147
and made it back in one piece.

31:40.064 --> 31:41.733
Almost one piece, sir.

31:42.609 --> 31:44.986
And to be frank,
I don't much like to talk about it.

31:45.695 --> 31:46.779
Your injury?

31:48.072 --> 31:49.282
Korea, sir.

31:50.241 --> 31:51.326
And why is that?

31:53.453 --> 31:54.996
Because we didn't finish the job.

31:57.332 --> 31:59.751
Well, that's why
we transferred you up here, Major.

32:00.710 --> 32:03.504
To test our new B-52, and if necessary,

32:03.588 --> 32:05.632
fly it straight
into the heart of the enemy.

32:05.715 --> 32:07.091
Finish what you started.

32:12.472 --> 32:13.765
Why the Air Force?

32:14.849 --> 32:16.392
I was raised on a farm.

32:16.726 --> 32:19.312
We had a family friend
that would come twice a month

32:19.395 --> 32:21.564
to dust the fields. So, my father,

32:22.065 --> 32:23.608
he wanted me to tag along. And I--

32:23.691 --> 32:25.401
I just took to it, you know?

32:27.195 --> 32:28.655
How about you, sir?

32:29.989 --> 32:31.032
My dad.

32:32.533 --> 32:33.576
Army man.

32:34.535 --> 32:37.956
Fought in every American conflict
from the Indian Wars to the Philippines,

32:39.082 --> 32:41.167
â€˜til they shoved him behind a desk.

32:41.250 --> 32:44.128
Only thing he loved more
than his country was his family.

32:45.463 --> 32:48.800
Told me the proudest moment of his life
was when I signed up to be a Doughboy.

32:52.428 --> 32:54.889
I can only imagine your father
felt the same way.

32:56.641 --> 32:57.892
He was proud, all right.

32:59.811 --> 33:01.646
He used to always say
there's nothing wrong

33:01.729 --> 33:05.566
with this country that can't be fixed
by what's right with this country.

33:09.946 --> 33:11.698
I aim to prove him right, sir.

33:36.848 --> 33:37.932
-Amen.
-Amen.

33:38.099 --> 33:39.308
-Amen.
-Amen.

33:49.736 --> 33:51.112
-Amen.
-Amen.

33:59.120 --> 34:00.872
My son, the bar mitzvah boy.

34:01.456 --> 34:02.832
How's the haftarah studying coming?

34:03.958 --> 34:05.043
Tastes good.

34:08.504 --> 34:10.089
Something the matter, Theodore?

34:13.509 --> 34:14.886
Can I ask you a weird question?

34:16.262 --> 34:17.304
Sure.

34:17.804 --> 34:19.599
Do you think somebody
could kidnap a kid

34:19.681 --> 34:20.850
and keep him underground?

34:22.185 --> 34:24.228
-Underground?
-What is wrong with you?

34:25.688 --> 34:29.859
Yeah, just keep him there,
in the sewers for months and months,

34:29.942 --> 34:31.485
hurting him or...

34:32.737 --> 34:33.905
I don't know.

34:35.114 --> 34:36.991
Have you ever heard
of something like that?

34:38.534 --> 34:41.496
Your grandparents escaped Buchenwald,

34:41.996 --> 34:43.956
their entire families murdered,

34:44.791 --> 34:46.793
the skin of Jewish prisoners

34:48.085 --> 34:49.462
used for lampshades.

34:50.505 --> 34:51.589
What?

34:52.590 --> 34:53.841
Lampshades.

34:56.469 --> 34:57.637
We are Jews, Theodore.

34:57.720 --> 35:00.723
We know better than anyone
the real horrors of this world.

35:03.559 --> 35:05.478
Reality is terrifying enough as it is.

35:08.856 --> 35:10.274
Cut it out with the fantasy.

36:50.791 --> 36:52.168
I can't believe we're related.

37:26.410 --> 37:27.787
I'm next, right?

37:29.413 --> 37:30.915
-So, now you believe me.
-Listen, Lilly,

37:30.998 --> 37:32.667
I've known this guy since first grade.

37:32.750 --> 37:33.918
And I know when he's lying,

37:34.001 --> 37:37.004
and he is not lying
about this lampshade shit.

37:37.088 --> 37:38.339
We have to tell someone.

37:38.422 --> 37:40.758
-No one's gonna believe us.
-What if we go to our parents?

37:41.217 --> 37:44.428
If I tell anyone about all of this,
I'll wind up right back at Juniper Hill.

37:45.137 --> 37:47.014
Maybe you guys will be in there with me.

37:48.099 --> 37:49.934
I can't go to the loony bin, Teddy.

37:50.017 --> 37:52.520
I couldn't make it
through goddamn sleepaway camp.

37:52.812 --> 37:54.063
Okay.

37:55.064 --> 37:56.774
We don't tell anyone,

37:57.483 --> 37:59.402
until we figure out
what really happened to Matty.

38:02.196 --> 38:03.281
And how do we do that?

38:05.950 --> 38:07.576
I think I might know where to start.

38:23.968 --> 38:25.011
You see anything?

38:25.094 --> 38:26.679
Teddy, did you know
that there are more than

38:26.762 --> 38:28.264
a hundred books in this library?

38:28.431 --> 38:30.725
No way. More than a hundred?

38:31.350 --> 38:33.185
And did you know
that some of them have pictures

38:33.269 --> 38:34.520
but most of them don't have pictures?

38:34.645 --> 38:35.646
What is she doing here?

38:35.730 --> 38:37.106
My folks couldn't find a sitter, okay?

38:37.189 --> 38:38.983
And did you know
that when you take out a book,

38:39.191 --> 38:41.360
you have to sign your name?
I can sign mine in cursive.

38:41.444 --> 38:44.280
Miss Carmel says
I have the best handwriting in the class.

38:45.614 --> 38:46.699
Phil.

38:48.451 --> 38:51.662
Hey, Suze, I need a really good handwriter

38:51.746 --> 38:53.664
to help me with finding a book.

38:53.748 --> 38:56.792
It's called Bucket Full of Muffins.

39:00.338 --> 39:01.339
I'll do it.

39:05.343 --> 39:06.385
She'll never find it.

39:09.513 --> 39:11.140
Wait, there it is.

39:15.853 --> 39:17.980
They thought it could be
a runaway initially,

39:18.064 --> 39:19.648
but when he never turned up
anywhere else,

39:19.732 --> 39:21.692
they presumed homicide.

39:23.652 --> 39:25.071
That means murder.

39:26.572 --> 39:29.158
They thought
it could have been Matty's dad.

39:29.700 --> 39:32.620
Could have been a drifter,
but they never found anyone.

39:32.703 --> 39:34.080
"According to police sources,

39:34.163 --> 39:36.540
the boy was last seen
the night of January 4th

39:36.624 --> 39:39.835
at the Capitol Theater
by the daughter of a theater employee,

39:39.919 --> 39:41.962
an unidentified 12-year-old girl."

39:46.258 --> 39:47.468
Who's that?

39:48.552 --> 39:49.887
Matty Clements?

39:50.721 --> 39:53.015
Jesus Christ, get the hell out of here!

39:53.265 --> 39:54.433
-Get out!

39:55.351 --> 39:57.103
What? What did we say?

39:58.604 --> 40:00.648
Do you know how many times
the police came round

40:00.731 --> 40:03.317
about that boy?
Trying to fix it on my pops?

40:04.276 --> 40:07.238
Did your newspaper article
mention anything about that?

40:08.280 --> 40:10.282
I really only skimmed, so--

40:10.366 --> 40:11.492
Just leave!

40:12.118 --> 40:13.619
Can we go get a shake now?

40:15.538 --> 40:18.124
See, I told you guys
this was a bad idea,

40:18.290 --> 40:20.459
chasing a song you heard
in the fucking sewers.

40:24.004 --> 40:25.005
What did you say?

40:31.303 --> 40:32.304
It was a song.

40:33.639 --> 40:36.016
I heard Matty singing it
a couple nights back.

40:36.892 --> 40:38.811
From the drainpipe in my tub.

40:41.564 --> 40:43.023
You heard him too?

40:45.359 --> 40:49.363
I don't know if it was Matty,
but I did hear voices

40:50.197 --> 40:53.909
in the basement of the Capitol,
in the pipes.

40:55.327 --> 40:59.582
Kids laughing, crying, calling my name.

41:03.544 --> 41:05.254
What song was he singing?

42:38.222 --> 42:41.684
The new B-52. G-class.
They transferred you up here to fly it.

42:41.767 --> 42:44.645
If you wanna walk out of here alive,
you're gonna give us the specs.

42:44.728 --> 42:49.108
Speed, range, flight ceiling,
payload, arms, everything.

42:49.191 --> 42:50.317
Understand?

42:50.818 --> 42:53.112
I'd understand you better
if you took off that mask.

42:53.195 --> 42:54.947
The specs. Now.

42:55.614 --> 42:57.283
It's classified.

43:11.964 --> 43:13.591
This isn't a fucking game.

43:13.924 --> 43:17.052
The specs, or I pull the trigger
on the count of three.

43:19.930 --> 43:20.973
One.

43:28.689 --> 43:29.732
Two.

43:33.110 --> 43:34.778
You're gonna have to pull that trigger.

43:38.324 --> 43:40.159
-Leroy!
-Yo, Lee, what's going on?

43:40.242 --> 43:41.994
Lee, open the door!

43:46.123 --> 43:48.459
Open the door! Yo, Lee,
what's going on in there?

43:48.542 --> 43:50.044
Open the door!

43:50.127 --> 43:51.837
Lee, open the fucking door!

44:07.269 --> 44:08.646
Get the fuck out of here!

44:09.313 --> 44:11.315
Yeah, that's what I thought.

44:15.569 --> 44:16.820
Saved your ass again.

44:18.030 --> 44:20.157
-Fuck you, Pauly.
-Who the fuck were those guys?

44:20.240 --> 44:21.408
I don't know.

44:22.785 --> 44:24.286
Jesus Christ.

44:27.706 --> 44:28.916
How's my hair?

44:30.626 --> 44:31.627
It's still greasy.

44:38.133 --> 44:39.426
So, where the hell are we going?

44:39.510 --> 44:41.970
You want me to tell you
or you want me to show you?

44:42.096 --> 44:44.348
Tell. One hundred percent tell.

44:44.431 --> 44:47.393
The song Matty was singing comes
from the movie The Music Man.

44:47.810 --> 44:49.978
We should have another print
up in the storage room.

44:52.231 --> 44:54.483
And why do we wanna watch
this stupid thing?

44:54.942 --> 44:56.527
I hate musicals.

44:57.403 --> 44:59.905
Because maybe Matty was trying
to tell us something.

45:11.041 --> 45:13.085
Holy crap, it's dark in here.

45:14.545 --> 45:16.547
Guys, isn't this breaking and entering?

45:16.630 --> 45:18.590
We didn't break anything.
It's just entering.

45:18.674 --> 45:20.759
-Don't be such a baby.
-Guys, stop.

45:21.260 --> 45:22.302
Let's just sit.

45:37.359 --> 45:38.444
Just a second!

45:38.527 --> 45:40.446
Loading up The Music Man!

45:46.076 --> 45:47.244
Teds, is that you?

45:48.829 --> 45:51.415
-Is he crying?
-What? No.

45:51.957 --> 45:53.208
Shut up, you guys.

45:55.127 --> 45:56.754
Lilly, are you okay?

45:58.297 --> 46:00.466
Yeah. No, I'm fine. I'm just...

46:02.301 --> 46:04.136
...thinking about Matty
and what happened,

46:04.219 --> 46:06.388
and what I could have
done different, and--

46:06.472 --> 46:07.639
Well, he needed me.

46:09.099 --> 46:10.934
And instead, I just sent him away.

46:11.977 --> 46:13.270
Then he was gone.

46:15.647 --> 46:16.982
What we did was worse.

46:18.859 --> 46:20.736
Maybe if we'd been there
like we said we would

46:20.819 --> 46:23.530
at his birthday, maybe things
would be different.

46:23.614 --> 46:25.407
It's nobody's fault, okay?

46:26.700 --> 46:29.995
Teds, it's not your fault.
Lilly, it isn't your fault either.

46:30.078 --> 46:32.122
We're here now. That's what matters.

46:32.206 --> 46:33.624
So just stop it, okay?

46:37.544 --> 46:38.754
Are you crying?

46:39.421 --> 46:41.089
What? No, I'm not crying.

